Amazon Web Services (AWS) is the world's most comprehensive cloud platform, providing on-demand technology services like computing power, database storage, and content delivery, allowing users to avoid maintaining physical data centers. It is used for hosting websites, running applications, data analytics, machine learning, and storing vast amounts of data, with a pay-as-you-go model.
The Jenkins project produces two release lines: Stable (LTS) and weekly. Depending on your organization's needs, one may be preferred over the other. See the links below for more information and recommendations about the release lines.
